 as 'one of the glamour debs.'"},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"Ex-wife Cookie killed 1941 in Newport plane crash","body":"Eighteen months after their December 1939 divorce, Cookie Young died July 1, 1941 in a plane crash near Matunuck Rhode Island. She was twenty-three. She had been flying in a Fairchild Model 24 monoplane in fog off Newport with Nicholas Embiricos, the Greek shipping heir. 'Cookie and her dog were thrown from the plane; Nicky died on the beach; Cookie died an hour later at South County Hospital of a fractured skull.' Her father Robert Ralph Young later died by suicide at his Palm Beach home."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Newport and Palm Beach social circles, four marriages","body":"Robert Ogden Bacon was born May 16, 1912 in Manhattan and active in the Newport and Palm Beach social circles characteristic of mid-twentieth-century American old-money. He had four marriages total, the Cookie Young match being his second. He died August 4, 1972 in Atlanta Georgia at age sixty and is buried at Mount Hebron Cemetery, Flushing Queens New York."}],"slug":"robert-bacon-1912"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}